prompt.user_prompt_template:
Below are {SAMPLE_SIZE} cleaned user reviews (id: text) for the Headspace app.

{numbered_reviews}

Group these reviews into exactly {NUM_GROUPS} thematic groups. Each group should represent a distinct type of user concern or situation. Each group must contain at least {MIN_PER_GROUP} review IDs.

Respond ONLY with a valid JSON object in exactly this format, no preamble:
{
  "groups": [
    {
      "group_id": "A1",
      "theme": "<short theme label>",
      "review_ids": [<list of integer IDs>],
      "example_reviews": ["<verbatim review text 1>", "<verbatim review text 2>"]
    }
  ]
}

Persona: {persona_name}
Description: {persona_description}
Goals: {persona_goals}
Pain Points: {persona_pain_points}
Constraints: {persona_constraints}
Derived from review group: {group_id} — '{group_theme}'

Generate exactly {REQS_PER_PERSONA} distinct software requirements for the Headspace app motivated by this persona. Each requirement must:
- Use 'The system shall...' phrasing
- Have specific, measurable acceptance criteria in Given/When/Then format
- Not use vague terms like 'fast', 'easy', 'better', or 'user-friendly'

Respond ONLY with a valid JSON array, no preamble:
[
  {
    "description": "The system shall ...",
    "acceptance_criteria": "Given ... When ... Then ..."
  }
]

Requirement ID: {requirement_id}
Description: {description}
Acceptance Criteria: {acceptance_criteria}
Source Persona: {source_persona}

Write exactly {TESTS_PER_REQ} test scenarios that validate this requirement. Each scenario should test a different situation (normal use and edge case). Steps must be real actions a tester performs in the Headspace mobile app.

Respond ONLY with valid JSON in this exact format:
[
  {
    "scenario": "Scenario title",
    "steps": ["Step 1", "Step 2", "Step 3"],
    "expected_result": "Expected outcome"
  }
]
